==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Littoral
<hw>Lit"to*ral</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>littoralis</ets>, <ets>litoralis</ets>, from <ets>littus</ets>,
<ets>litus</ets>, the seashore: cf. F. <ets>littoral</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a shore, as of the sea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Inhabiting the seashore, esp. the
zone between high-water and low-water mark.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Littorina</ent>⟦br⟧
